{"parse":{"title":"Andrea Doucet","pageid":25468768,"revid":857482352,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Andrea Doucet</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Canada\" title=\"Canada\">Canada</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Education</th><td>\nBA in Political Theory, <a href=\"/wiki/York_University\" title=\"York University\">York University</a><br />MA in International Development Studies, <a href=\"/wiki/Carleton_University\" title=\"Carleton University\">Carleton University</a>, PhD, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Cambridge\" title=\"University of Cambridge\">University of Cambridge</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Occupation</th><td class=\"role\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Canada_Research_Chair\" title=\"Canada Research Chair\">Canada Research Chair</a> in Gender, Work and Care</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Employer</th><td class=\"org\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Carleton_University\" title=\"Carleton University\">Carleton University</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Brock_University\" title=\"Brock University\">Brock University</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\n<span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.andreadoucet.com\">www<wbr />.andreadoucet<wbr />.com</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Andrea Doucet</b> (born c.1960) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Canadians\" title=\"Canadians\">Canadian</a> social scientist and writer. She is professor of sociology and <a href=\"/wiki/Gender_Studies\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gender Studies\">gender studies</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Brock_University\" title=\"Brock University\">Brock University</a>, and holds the <a href=\"/wiki/Canada_Research_Chair\" title=\"Canada Research Chair\">Canada Research Chair</a> in gender, work and care. She was also the editor of the academic journal <i><a href=\"/wiki/Fathering_(journal)\" title=\"Fathering (journal)\">Fathering</a></i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Education\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Education</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Research\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Research</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Selected_publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Awards\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Doucet was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Bathurst,_New_Brunswick\" title=\"Bathurst, New Brunswick\">Bathurst, New Brunswick</a>, Canada in 1960,<sup id=\"cite_ref-stcatharinesstandard_2011_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-stcatharinesstandard_2011-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> where she grew up in an anglophone family. Her sister is <a href=\"/wiki/BBC\" title=\"BBC\">BBC</a> journalist <a href=\"/wiki/Lyse_Doucet\" title=\"Lyse Doucet\">Lyse Doucet</a> <span class=\"noexcerpt\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Officer_of_the_Order_of_the_British_Empire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Officer of the Order of the British Empire\">OBE</a></span>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Education\">Education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Education\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Doucet completed her BA in political theory at <a href=\"/wiki/York_University\" title=\"York University\">York University</a> in Toronto and her MA in international development studies at Carleton University. She earned her <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">PhD</a> in social and political sciences in 1995 from Cambridge University.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1995 and 1996 Doucet was a post doctoral fellow and lecturer at Cambridge. From 1995 to 1998 she was an assistant professor of sociology at <a href=\"/wiki/Saint_Mary%27s_University_(Halifax)\" title=\"Saint Mary&#39;s University (Halifax)\">St. Mary's University</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Halifax,_Nova_Scotia\" title=\"Halifax, Nova Scotia\">Halifax, Nova Scotia</a>. At Carleton University, she was professor of sociology from 1998 to 2011.\n</p><p>She has been professor of sociology and <a href=\"/wiki/Gender_Studies\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gender Studies\">gender studies</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Brock_University\" title=\"Brock University\">Brock University</a> since 2011. She has also held the <a href=\"/wiki/Canada_Research_Chair\" title=\"Canada Research Chair\">Canada Research Chair</a> in gender, work and care since 2011. Doucet is recognized as an \"expert in caregiving and work-life balance\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-brocku_2011_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-brocku_2011-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>She was an editor of the now defunct academic journal, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Fathering_(journal)\" title=\"Fathering (journal)\">Fathering: a Journal of Theory, Research, and Practice about Men as Fathers</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-carleton_2009_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-carleton_2009-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2009, as sociology professor at <a href=\"/wiki/Carleton_University\" title=\"Carleton University\">Carleton University</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Ottawa,_Ontario\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ottawa, Ontario\">Ottawa, Ontario</a>, Doucet undertook a study entitled \"Bread and Roses Project\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> in which she tracked couples in which women were the primary earners using data from both Canada and the United States. In a 2010 interview with <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times</a></i>, Doucet observed that, \"With women taking on more earning and men taking on more caring, there's a lot of shifting and juggling. You can't just reverse the genders.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_Parker_Pope_2010_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT_Parker_Pope_2010-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> In an interview with the <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Post\" title=\"New York Post\">New York Post</a></i> Doucet explained that \"The ambiguity over who does what, and its accompanying stress, is to be expected as gender roles change.\"The 'mancession' has been difficult on couples. Many have told me that they did not expect to be in this situation. To suddenly have it sprung upon you because of job loss can lead to a rapid and stress-filled learning curve for both men and women.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYPOst_2010_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYPOst_2010-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> In her 2013 book  <i>Bread and Roses \u2014 And the Kitchen Sink</i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Doucet_Bread_2013_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Doucet_Bread_2013-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> based on the study, Doucet said, \"It's been just a steady progression of women's education going up and employment going up, but then quite a remarkable leap in women being primary breadwinners or shared primary breadwinners relates to the changes in the economy.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-postmedia_Proudfoot_2010_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-postmedia_Proudfoot_2010-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Research\">Research</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Research\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>From 1998-2002 she was the principal investigator of \"Fathers as Primary Caregivers\" which received a Canada <a href=\"/wiki/Social_Sciences_and_Humanities_Research_Council\" title=\"Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council\">Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council</a> (SSHRC),<sup id=\"cite_ref-carleton_2009_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-carleton_2009-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> the Canadian federal research funding agency.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Doucet, Andrea (2006). <i>Do men mother? fathering, care, and domestic responsibility</i>. Toronto, Ontario: <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Toronto_Press\" title=\"University of Toronto Press\">University of Toronto Press</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780802085467\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780802085467\">9780802085467</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Do+men+mother%3F+fathering%2C+care%2C+and+domestic+responsibility&amp;rft.place=Toronto%2C+Ontario&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Toronto+Press&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=9780802085467&amp;rft.aulast=Doucet&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Doucet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Doucet, Andrea; Siltanen, Janet (2008). <i>Gender relations in Canada: intersectionality and beyond</i>. Don Mills, Ontario: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195423204\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780195423204\">9780195423204</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Gender+relations+in+Canada%3A+intersectionality+and+beyond&amp;rft.place=Don+Mills%2C+Ontario&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=9780195423204&amp;rft.aulast=Doucet&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rft.au=Siltanen%2C+Janet&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Doucet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFDoucet2010\" class=\"citation\">Doucet, Andrea (2010), \"Taking off the maternal lens: engaging with Sara Ruddick on men and mothering\",  in <a href=\"/wiki/Andrea_O%27Reilly\" title=\"Andrea O&#39;Reilly\">O'Reilly, Andrea</a>, <i>Twenty-first-century motherhood experience, identity, policy, agency</i>, New York: Columbia University Press, pp.&#160;170\u2013180, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780231520478\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780231520478\">9780231520478</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Taking+off+the+maternal+lens%3A+engaging+with+Sara+Ruddick+on+men+and+mothering&amp;rft.btitle=Twenty-first-century+motherhood+experience%2C+identity%2C+policy%2C+agency&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=170-180&amp;rft.pub=Columbia+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=9780231520478&amp;rft.aulast=Doucet&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Doucet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=VAI3ON-OnlsC&amp;pg=PA170\">Preview.</a></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFDoucetMcKayTremblay2011\" class=\"citation\">Doucet, Andrea; McKay, Lindsey; Tremblay, Diane-Gabrielle (2011), \"Canada and Quebec: two policies, one country\",  in Moss, Peter; Kamerman, Sheila B., <i>The politics of parental leave policies: children, parenting, gender and the labour market</i>, Bristol: Policy, pp.&#160;33\u201350, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781847429032\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781847429032\">9781847429032</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Canada+and+Quebec%3A+two+policies%2C+one+country&amp;rft.btitle=The+politics+of+parental+leave+policies%3A+children%2C+parenting%2C+gender+and+the+labour+market&amp;rft.place=Bristol&amp;rft.pages=33-50&amp;rft.pub=Policy&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.isbn=9781847429032&amp;rft.aulast=Doucet&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rft.au=McKay%2C+Lindsey&amp;rft.au=Tremblay%2C+Diane-Gabrielle&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Doucet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards\">Awards</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Awards\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>2007 John Porter Tradition of Excellence Book Award from the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Canadian_Sociological_Association&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Canadian Sociological Association (page does not exist)\">Canadian Sociological Association</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Doucet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-stcatharinesstandard_2011-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-stcatharinesstandard_2011_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Fraser, Tom (October 13, 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2011/10/13/brock-gets-world-renowned-working-family-researcher\">\"Brock gets world-renowned working family researcher\"</a>. <i>St Catharine's Standard</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=St+Catharine%27s+Standard&amp;rft.atitle=Brock+gets+world-renowned+working+family+researcher&amp;rft.date=2011-10-13&amp;rft.aulast=Fraser&amp;rft.aufirst=Tom&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.stcatharinesstandard.ca%2F2011%2F10%2F13%2Fbrock-gets-world-renowned-working-family-researcher&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Doucet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Doucet, Andrea (2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=G1p3v2soHToC&amp;pg=PR11\"><i>Do Men Mother?: Fathering, Care, and Domestic Responsibility</i></a>. University of Toronto Press. p.&#160;xi. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780802085467\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780802085467\">9780802085467</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Do+Men+Mother%3F%3A+Fathering%2C+Care%2C+and+Domestic+Responsibility&amp;rft.pages=xi&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Toronto+Press&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=9780802085467&amp;rft.aulast=Doucet&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DG1p3v2soHToC%26pg%